Ask for an SDP offer to a NetworkConnection, calling SdpPortManager.generateSdpOffer().
In the process, a listener is attached to the NetworkConnection. This listener will notify the NC when an event comes in. The listener remains attached after the call (this is a side-effect).

Match/loopback the local/remote SDPs of the given pair of NetworkConnections.

Parameters:
ncPair - The two NetworkConnections to operate on
forceInbandDTMFs - if true, strip telephone-event from SDP
offerByNC0 - if true, ncPair[0] is required to provide an offer, which is proposed to ncPair[1]. If false, ncPair[1] provides the first offer.
